What you need to know:

Nairobi West, known for its fast-paced nightlife, fell silent in March after the government ordered a dusk-to-dawn curfew from 7 pm to 5 am.But the nightlife in the suburb and others across the capital is being revived after the government reopened entertainment spots and bars on September 28 and shortened the curfew hours by two hours, from 11 pm to 4 am. 